o states of acute and chronic illness. Separate chapters are devoted to each of the body’s systems in detail: nervous, endocrine, cardiovascular, respiratory, renal, gastrointestinal, musculoskeletal, reproductive, and immune. Through a series of real-life examples, the book also shows the importance of maintaining careful medical records for health care professionals, scientists, and patients alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHuman physiology. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aOur Marvelous Bodies, An Introduction to the Physiology of Human Health, GARY F. MERRILL, cell biology, neuroscience, structure of body's major systems, function pf body's major systems, care of the body's major systems, human body, physiology, human health, medical facts alongside personal stories, basics of feedback control systems, homeostasis, physiological gradients, body’s functioning, optimal, healthy conditions for body, acute illnesses, chronic illnesses, nervous system, endocrine system, cardiovascular system, respiratory system, renal system, gastrointestinal system, musculoskeletal system, reproductive system, immune system, medical records, health care professionals, scientists, patients.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081354470040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813544700423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813544700/original  a978-3-11-068861-0  Rutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles